==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monkey-pot
<hw>Mon"key-pot`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>The fruit of two South American trees (<spn>Lecythis Ollaria</spn>,
and <spn>Lecythis Zabucajo</spn>), which have for their fruit large,
pot-shaped, woody capsules containing delicious nuts, and opening almost
explosively by a circular lid at the top. Vases and pots are made of
this capsule.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monkey's puzzle</ent>⟦br⟧
